FBIS4-38103 "drnes124_s_94013" FBIS-NES-94-124 Daily Report 23 Jun 1994 Iran Amphibious Exercise Successfully Concluded Amphibious Exercise Successfully Concluded LD2306103294 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 23 Jun 94 LD2306103294 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Persian BFN [Text] The amphibious Zafar-1 joint military exercise, which started in Persian Gulf waters and the strategic Strait of Hormoz on 30 Khordad [20 June], was concluded successfully today. Light and heavy vessels, fast assault boats, rangers, and commandoes of the Armed Forces and the Islamic Revolution Guard Corps, and a number of fighter-bombers of the Islamic Republic Air Force took part in the exercise. Operations were carried out in six phases, involving the control of communication routes and navy equipment; dispatching units of light vessels; air and surface bombardment of communication routes, vital positions, and installations of an imaginary enemy; reconnaissance and mine-sweeping operations by special teams; and capturing the positions and sea rescue operations of the vessels of the imaginary enemy. The Zafar-1 maneuver is one of a series of joint annual exercises of the Armed Forces and the Guards Corps, aimed at raising defensive capabilities and exchanging experience and military know-how.
